1 (1) Any person who violates any of the provisions of this chapter or administrative
2 regulations adopted under this chapter shall be fined not less than fifty dollars ($50)
3 nor more than two hundred dollars ($200). [After July 15, 2000, ]Any person who
4 violates KRS 235.230 shall be fined not less than fifteen dollars ($15) nor more
5 than one hundred dollars ($100) and each day the violation continues may
6 constitute a separate offense.
7 (2) (a) Any person who violates KRS 235.240 shall not be subject to the penalties of
8 KRS Chapter 189A but shall be guilty of a separate offense and subject to:
9 1. For the first offense, a fine of two hundred dollars ($200) to two
10 hundred fifty dollars ($250) or imprisonment for twenty-four (24) hours;
11 2. For the second offense[ for the first offense], a fine of three hundred
12 fifty dollars ($350) to five hundred dollars ($500) or imprisonment for
13 forty-eight (48) hours; and
14 3. For the third and subsequent offenses,[ for the second offense, and] a
15 fine of six hundred dollars ($600) to one thousand dollars ($1,000) or
16 imprisonment in the county jail for not less than thirty (30) days, or
17 both[, for the third or subsequent offense].
18 (b) Refusal to submit to a breath alcohol analysis or similar test in violation of
19 KRS 235.240(3) shall be deemed an offense.
20 (3) (a) A person may, in addition to or in lieu of the penalties specified in subsection
21 (1) or (5) of this section, be required to take a safe-boating course approved
22 by the department or offered by the United States Coast Guard, Coast Guard
23 Auxiliary, or U.S. Power Squadron and to present the court a certificate
24 documenting successful completion of the course.
25 (b) A person shall, in addition to the penalties of subsection (2) of this section, be
26 required to take a safe-boating course offered by the department and to
27 present the court a certificate documenting successful completion of the
