4 (4) [After July 15, 2000, ]Any person who violates KRS 235.420 or 235.430 shall be
5 fined:
6 (a) For the first offense, not less than fifteen dollars ($15) nor more than one
7 hundred dollars ($100);
8 (b) For the second offense,[. A person who violates KRS 235.420 or 235.430
9 shall be fined] not less than one hundred dollars ($100) nor more than three
10 hundred dollars ($300); and
11 (c) For the third and each subsequent offense,[ for the second offense, and] not
12 less than three hundred dollars ($300) nor more than five hundred dollars
13 ($500)[ for the third or any subsequent offense].
14 (5) Any person failing to obey a citation issued in accordance with KRS 235.315 shall
15 be guilty of a separate offense and shall be fined not less than fifty dollars ($50) nor
16 more than two hundred dollars ($200).
17 (6) Any person who makes a false statement regarding a marine boat toilet on the
18 application for registration or renewal registration for a motorboat shall be fined
19 one hundred dollars ($100). This penalty shall be separate from any other penalty
20 that may be applicable for violation of this chapter.
21 (7) Any person who resists, obstructs, interferes with, threatens, attempts to intimidate,
22 or in any other manner interferes with any officer in the discharge of his duties,
23 other than a criminal homicide or an assault against an officer enforcing the
24 provisions of this chapter, KRS Chapter 150, or the administrative regulations
25 issued under either of these chapters, shall be guilty of a Class A misdemeanor.
26 (8) Any person who commits a criminal homicide or an assault against an officer
27 enforcing the provisions of this chapter, KRS Chapter 150, or the administrative
