3 (9) Any person who violates KRS 235.203 shall be fined fifty dollars ($50).
4 SECTION 3. A NEW SECTION OF KRS 15.530 TO 15.590 IS CREATED TO
5 READ AS FOLLOWS:
6 In addition to all other required dispatches and reports, a public safety
7 telecommunicator who receives a report of an accident involving a motorboat or vessel
8 on any waters within the jurisdiction of the Commonwealth shall immediately report
9 the accident, or cause a report of the accident to be made, to the post of the Department
10 of Kentucky State Police covering where the accident occurred.
11 Section 4. This Act may be cited as Keegan's Law.
